        public Rule.Builder withParams(java.lang.String... classNames)
        Specify the exact parameters to match. Needed for differentiating overloaded methods.
        Parameters:
        classNames - The fully qualified classnames of the params for the method being instrumented
        Returns:
        the Rule.Builder NOTE: If withParams(String...) is called for the builder, method match type will be ignored and behave as though SDKStringMatchType.EQUALS is set.

      • atLineNumber

        public Rule.Builder atLineNumber(int lineNum)
        This method is used to define a specific line number in the file to instrument. This method can be used in conjunction with isAbsoluteLineNumber(boolean)
        Parameters:
        lineNum - the line number
        Returns:
        the builder for chained build.
        See Also:
        isAbsoluteLineNumber(boolean)

      • isAbsoluteLineNumber

        public Rule.Builder isAbsoluteLineNumber(boolean isAbsLineNum)
        This method is used to defined whether the line number specified by atLineNumber(int) is an absolute line number or a relative line number relative to the start of the method. Note that the start of the method is actually the first "meaningful" instruction. Variable declaration, not instantiation, are not "meaningful" instructions.
        Parameters:
        isAbsLineNum - true if the line number is absolute
        Returns:
        the builder for chained build.

      • atLocalVariable

        public Rule.Builder atLocalVariable(java.lang.String name,
                                    boolean read,
                                    int occurrence)
        This method is used to defined where at a local variable match to instrument.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the local variable.
        read - true if we are matching a local variable read, false for write.
        occurrence - the number of occurrence of the local variable read or write.
        Returns:
        the builder for chained build.

      • collectLocalVariables

        public Rule.Builder collectLocalVariables(java.lang.String[] vars)
        This method is used to define what local variables we would like to collect. Note that sometimes the local variable names gets changed by the compiler or obfuscator. As a result, some local variables cannot be collected.
        Parameters:
        vars - the array of local variable names
        Returns:
